  • Class
    Description
    DataConsistencyChecks
    Interface used by bean validation @GroupSequence representing a group of constraints that check the consistency of data, for example whether a field references an object which exists in the system.
    DataFormatChecks
    Interface used by bean validation @GroupSequence representing a group of constraints that check the format of data, for example whether a field contains an integer.
    DoesNotExist
    Type constraint that is used to verify whether an object already exists in the system with unique properties matching those used in a DTO being used to create a new object or update an existing object.
    Exists
    Field constraint used to check whether an object referenced by the key value in the annotated field exists in the system.
    ValidDateRange
    Constraint that is used to verify the date represented by the Optional<String> identified by firstDatePropertyName occurs before or on the same date as the Optional<String> identified by secondDatePropertyName.
    ValidDateString
    Field constraint that verifies that if the Optional contains a value then it is a valid date string in DateTimeFormatter.ISO_LOCAL_DATE format.
    ValidUriString
    Field constraint that verifies that the field contains a string that can be parsed as a valid absolute URI.
